punitive in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">media market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> because the TV licence fee is effectively a tax</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The BBC should move </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">without delay </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">to a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> subscription service which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">simply </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> withdrawn if a subscriber fails to keep up payments.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">5.0 Dangers of market dominance by the BBC</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">5.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> The dominant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">size</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> of the BBC stifles</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> media market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> poses a threat to democracy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">he</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> BBC, just like every other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; f